<BlogPost
  title="Getting Started with SENTRA in 5 Minutes"
  description="Install SENTRA, scan your code, and enforce a quality gate — all in under 5 minutes."
  date="2026-03-05"
>

<h2>What you'll build</h2>

<p>By the end of this tutorial, you'll have SENTRA scanning your Python project against OWASP Top 10 security rules and blocking non-compliant PRs in CI/CD.</p>

<p>Total time: about 5 minutes.</p>

<h2>1. Install (30 seconds)</h2>

<pre><code>pip install sentra</code></pre>

<p>That's it. SENTRA is a single Python package with no external dependencies for core functionality. Both <code>sentra</code> and <code>guard</code> commands are available.</p>

<h2>2. Initialize (30 seconds)</h2>

<pre><code>cd your-project
sentra init</code></pre>

<p>The setup wizard asks 5 questions:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>DevOps Platform</strong> — Choose your work item tracker (GitHub, Azure DevOps, Jira, or none)</li>
  <li><strong>Project Type</strong> — General, Medical device, or SOC2/Fintech</li>
  <li><strong>Governance Profile</strong> — Strict, Standard, or Permissive</li>
  <li><strong>Output Directory</strong> — Where scan results are written (default: <code>out/</code>)</li>
  <li><strong>Pre-commit Hook</strong> — Whether to scan on every commit</li>
</ol>

<p>For a quick start, accept all defaults. This creates <code>.guard.yaml</code> in your project root.</p>

<h2>3. Enable OWASP rules (15 seconds)</h2>

<pre><code>sentra add-pack owasp-top-10</code></pre>

<p>This enables 22 security rules covering all OWASP Top 10 categories: injection, auth failures, cryptographic issues, SSRF, and more.</p>

<h2>4. Scan (30 seconds)</h2>

<pre><code>sentra scan</code></pre>

<p>SENTRA evaluates every Python file against the enabled rules. You'll see output like:</p>

<pre><code>CRITICAL  OWASP-A03-005  src/api.py:42    eval() executes arbitrary code
HIGH      OWASP-A01-001  src/auth.py:18   Hardcoded credentials detected
MEDIUM    OWASP-A02-001  src/crypto.py:9  Weak hashing algorithm (MD5)

3 findings (1 critical, 1 high, 1 medium)
Next: sentra gate — enforce quality gates</code></pre>

<p>Results are written to <code>out/findings.json</code> (machine-readable) and <code>out/report.md</code> (human-readable).</p>

<h2>5. Gate (15 seconds)</h2>

<pre><code>sentra gate</code></pre>

<p>The gate exits with code 0 (pass) or 1 (fail). By default, <code>critical</code> and <code>high</code> findings fail the gate. Fix those findings, re-run, and the gate passes.</p>

<h2>6. Add to CI/CD (2 minutes)</h2>

<p>Add this to your GitHub Actions workflow:</p>

<pre><code># .github/workflows/sentra.yml
name: SENTRA Gate
on: [pull_request]

jobs:
  gate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with:
          python-version: "3.12"
      - run: pip install sentra
      - run: sentra gate --git-range "origin/main...HEAD"</code></pre>

<p>Every PR is now gated. Non-compliant code can't merge.</p>

<h2>Bonus: Dashboard</h2>

<pre><code>pip install "sentra[server]"
sentra serve</code></pre>

<p>Open <a href="http://localhost:8000/dashboard">http://localhost:8000/dashboard</a> for a web UI showing findings, rules, governance policies, and scan trends.</p>

